    "message_1": "Suppose you have the following set of data points (x,y): {(0, 3), (1, 5), (2, 1), (3, 2)}. Use Lagrange interpolation to find f(1.5).",
    "message_2": "To find f(1.5) using Lagrange interpolation, we will use the formula:\n\nf(x) = L(x) = Σ [y_i * l_i(x)]\n\nwhere l_i(x) = Π [(x - x_j) / (x_i - x_j)] for j ≠ i\n\nThe given data points are (x0, y0) = (0, 3), (x1, y1) = (1, 5), (x2, y2) = (2, 1), and (x3, y3) = (3, 2).\n\nFirst, we will find the l_i(x) terms:\n\nl_0(x) = [(x - x1)(x - x2)(x - x3)] / [(x0 - x1)(x0 - x2)(x0 - x3)] = [(x - 1)(x - 2)(x - 3)] / [(0 - 1)(0 - 2)(0 - 3)] = (x - 1)(x - 2)(x - 3) / 6\n\nl_1(x) = [(x - x0)(x - x2)(x - x3)] / [(x1 - x0)(x1 - x2)(x1 - x3)] = [(x - 0)(x - 2)(x - 3)] / [(1 - 0)(1 - 2)(1 - 3)] = x(x - 2)(x - 3) / -2\n\nl_2(x) = [(x - x0)(x - x1)(x - x3)] / [(x2 - x0)(x2 - x1)(x2 - x3)] = [(x - 0)(x - 1)(x - 3)] / [(2 - 0)(2 - 1)(2 - 3)] = (x)(x - 1)(x - 3) / 2\n\nl_3(x) = [(x - x0)(x - x1)(x - x2)] / [(x3 - x0)(x3 - x1)(x3 - x2)] = [(x - 0)(x - 1)(x - 2)] / [(3 - 0)(3 - 1)(3 - 2)] = (x)(x - 1)(x - 2) / 6\n\nNow we will find f(1.5) using the Lagrange interpolation formula:\n\nf(1.5) = 3 * l_0(1.5) + 5 * l_1(1.5) + 1 * l_2(1.5) + 2 * l_3(1.5)\n\nf(1.5) = 3 * [(1.5 - 1)(1.5 - 2)(1.5 - 3) / 6] + 5 * [(1.5)(1.5 - 2)(1.5 - 3) / -2] + 1 * [(1.5)(1.5 - 1)(1.5 - 3) / 2] + 2 * [(1.5)(1.5 - 1)(1.5 - 2) / 6]\n\nf(1.5) = 3 * [-0.5 * -1.5 * -2.5 / 6] + 5 * [1.5 * -0.5 * -1.5 / -2] + 1 * [1.5 * 0.5 * -1.5 / 2] + 2 * [1.5 * 0.5 * -0.5 / 6]\n\nf(1.5) = 3 * [1.875 / 6] - 5 * [1.125 / 2] + 1 * [-0.5625 / 2] + 2 * [-0.1875 / 6]\n\nf(1.5) = 0.9375 - 2.8125 - 0.28125 - 0.0625\n\nf(1.5) = -2.21875\n\nSo, using Lagrange interpolation, f(1.5) ≈ -2.21875."
